    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I'm not sure about that part. I agree that we should not have any flickering of UI, but not sure delaying the display until everything is ready is the way to go.\n\nWith events as proposed it will be up to the user to do it or not (display: none all widgets, then show them with or without css transition).\n\n> I did not experience the widget flickering, could you provide an example?\n\nRight now the widgets are empty containers that are filled later on when everything is ready. So you can see the border flickering:\n- first load, has empty containers with borders\n- instantsearch.js loads an init, widgets are filled up\n\nI think if you throttle your connection in chrome you should see it.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-05T09:07:00Z",
